<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Backup and Restore the Evernote</font></b></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#ff2f92">Important:</font> Under the MAC OS X the Evernote configuration</div><div>                  and database is located in:</div><div>                <font style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">  /Users/khasanov/Library/Application Support/com.evernote.Evernote</font></div><div>                  You must backup this directory if you want the full recovery.</div><div>Step 1. You must install the same version of the Evernote!</div><div>Step 2. Delete the “<font color="#941100">com.evernote.Evernote</font>” created by new installation.</div><div>Step 3. Copy the  “<span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">com.evernote.Evernote</span>” from a backup loation and replace it.</div><div><br /></div><div>Note: If you install the latest ( or more update) version of the Evernote, it NOT work! </div><div>          There is the file called “verion” and it will tell you what version its using.</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 18px;">Evernote FAQ</font></b></div><div><br /></div><div>How to create a local Notebook?</div><div>Click on “Option” (Alt) and then -&gt; File -&gt; New Local Notebook.</div><div>( It won’t show up if you just click on File ) </div></en-note>